Competition: Liga MX

*Mexico 1996/97

*     The 1996-97 Mexican Football League (Division 1) is
*split into two different tournaments (Winter 1996 and Summer
*1997).  In each tournament, a 17-game regular season will
*be followed by a playoff to determine the champion.

*     Playoff qualification for each tournament will be
*determined by the following criteria:
*
* (a) The winner of every group (4 in total) goes right to the
*     quarter-finals, that is, has a 1st-round bye.
*
* (b) The runner-up of every group goes to the playoffs as well.
*     The top two runner-ups get a 1st-round bye. The third and
*     fourth runner up (RU.3 & RU.4) might play in the 1st-round
*     playoff against two wild card teams.
*
* (c) The top two teams of the remaining ten not yet considered
*     will go to the 1st-round playoff ONLY if they have a better
*     overall standing than that of the lowest qualified team
*     according to (a) and (b) above.  They are tagged WC.1 and WC.2
*     (wild cards) according to their final overall standing.
*
* (d) Every match-up is played in a home-to-home series with the
*     following tie-breaker criteria:
*
*          (i) Aggregate score.
*         (ii) Away goals.
*        (iii) Final overall standing.
*
*     Therefore, every series (except the final) will be decided
*     after 180 minutes of action (no extra time).  Tie-breaker
*     (ii) and (iii) are removed for the final, allowing for the typical
*     extra-time period plus penalty shots should it be necessary.


