* The team with the lowest percentage (PTGE) at the end
* of the regular season is relegated to Division 1-A.
 
*   PTGE = Total of points earned from the 1994-95 through
*          the 1996-97 season divided by the total of games
*          played during that period.  Only regular season,
*          Division 1 matches are considered.  Points are
*          based on 2 points per each game won and 1 point
*          per each game tied.
* 
*   MN = Magic number of points needed to avoid relegation.
*        R := Relegated


